# OpenAI API Configuration
# Get your API key from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your-openai-api-key-here

# Vector Store ID (Required for Week 4 - File Search capabilities)
# Create a vector store at: https://platform.openai.com/storage
VECTOR_STORE_ID=vs_your-vector-store-id-here

# Optional: Perplexity API (Week 3 - Alternative search provider)
# Get your API key from: https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
PERPLEXITY_API_KEY=your-perplexity-api-key-here

# Optional: Google AI Studio (Week 3)
# Get your API key from: https://makersuite.google.com/app/apikey
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your-google-api-key-here

# Optional: Anthropic API (Week 3)
# Get your API key from: https://console.anthropic.com/
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=your-anthropic-api-key-here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file and rename it to ".env" (without .example)
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. Never commit the .env file to version control (it's in .gitignore)
# 4. At minimum, you need OPENAI_API_KEY to get started
